The paper proposes a novel method for imputing missing data using Generative Adversarial Nets (GAN), which is a popular framework in machine learning and falls under the category of deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of additional information in the form of a hint vector, which is a form of data preprocessing and falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The method is tested on various datasets, which involves image data, and hence, the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves the use of statistical techniques for imputing missing data, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
